CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper October 19, 1974, pg. 19, reads: "Subject Is Jazz - Tenor sax jazz artist Stanley Turrentine was welcomed back to Pittsburgh by club owner Walt Harper (right) when the famed musician appeared at Walt Harper's Attic last week.  The two hometown musicians are shown at the Attic and the subject of the course was - what else - Jazz. - Harris photo."The portraits on the wall include Duke Ellington, Benny Goodman, and Louis Armstrong.
TitMainTitle: Stanley Turrentine with saxophone and Walt Harper at microphone in Walt Harper's Attic with large portraits of musicians and sign reading "Sesame Street" on back wall
